Customuse Ltd (“
Customuse
”, “
We
”, “
Us
”, “
Our
”) is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. This Privacy Notice (the “
Notice
”) together with Our Terms of Service sets out the basis on which any personal data We collect from you, or that you provide to Us, via our applications, this website (https://customuse.com) (“
Website
”), Discord bot, and related services (collectively referred as Our “
Services
” or Our “
Products
”) and communications with you, will be processed by Us. PLEASE READ THIS NOTICE CAREFULLY TO UNDERSTAND OUR VIEWS AND PRACTICES REGARDING YOUR PERSONAL DATA AND HOW IT APPLIES TO OUR PRODUCTS AND SERVICES.
From time to time, We may develop new or offer additional services. If the introduction of these new or additional services results in any material change to the way We collect or process your personal data, We will provide you with more information or additional terms or policies. Unless otherwise stated, when We introduce these new or additional services, they will be subject to this Notice.
Customuse Ltd is the controller and responsible for your personal data. Our contact details are:
Customuse Ltd
130 Old Street, London
EC1V 9BD, United Kingdom
privacy@customuse.com
We may collect and process the following data about you:
You may give Us information about you by taking actions or filling in forms while using Our Products or by corresponding with Us by email, social media (when getting in touch with Our community team) or otherwise. This may include information you provide when you create or use a Customuse account, participate in discussion boards, or other social media functions on our Website, access articles and other resources, and requests for customer support and technical assistance:
Name, email address, username and password, billing information, log-in credentials, communications and marketing preferences.
Visual information through the images that you post using Our Products, including your profile pictures.
Any other personal information you choose to directly provide to Us in connection with your use of Our Products.
Every time you use Our Products, We may automatically collect the following information:
Technical information, including the Internet protocol (IP) address used to connect your computer to the Internet, browser type and version, time zone setting, browser plug-in types and versions, operating system and platform, cookies, Discord username and discord unique identifier when you access our Discord bot.
Information about your visit, including the full Uniform Resource Locators (URL) clickstream to, through and from Our Website (including date and time); products or services you viewed or searched for; page response times, download errors, length of visits to certain pages, page interaction information (such as scrolling, clicks, and mouse-overs), methods used to browse away from the page, and any email address used to contact Us (whether directly or through the use of third party-analytics tools) to help us measure traffic and usage trends for the Service.
We may collect the following information from third party sources:
Authentication partners - if you register for or log into Our Products using third party credentials (e.g. Google or Apple), We will import your information from such a third party to help create your account with Us.
Payment partners
-
if you purchase a subscription to Our Services, you will need to provide payment information (e.g., financial account details, shipping information) to process your subscription. We use third-party payment providers to process payments. We may receive information associated with your payment information, such as billing address and transaction information, but we do not directly store payment information. Payment information is stored and processed by Our payment providers on Our behalf.
Aggregated data - We may obtain certain analytical data, web user stats, such as cookie ID or other analytics from third-party analytics service providers that enables Us to improve Our Services, provide dashboard and overview information and review how content has been viewed.
We do not intend to process any special categories of data.
It is important that the personal data We hold about you is accurate and current. Please keep Us informed if your personal data changes during your relationship with Us.
We use the information We collect about you in the following ways:
To provide you with Our Services and display content you create and post on Our Services and social media;
To process and manage payments (which are processed and stored by Our third-party payment processors on Our behalf) and otherwise to service your purchase orders including but not limited to handling refund requests that you submit to us or to Our third-party processors on Our behalf such as Apple;
To promote and drive engagement and to make suggestions and recommendations to you about Our Products that may interest you;
To allow you to participate in the community and other interactive features of Our Services, when you choose to do so;
For internal operations, including troubleshooting, data analytics, testing, research, statistical and survey purposes;
To measure or understand the effectiveness of advertising and content We serve to you and others, and to deliver relevant advertising to you, where you have expressly agreed to receive advertising; and/or
For matters that We are required to use your information by law.
