Legal obligation
We will keep your personal data secure by taking appropriate technical and organisational measures against its unauthorised or unlawful processing and against its accidental loss, destruction or damage.
Our Services are hosted on secure AWS servers located in Frankfurt. The data that We collect from you may be transferred to, and stored at, a destination outside the UK and European Economic Area (“EEA”). It may also be processed by staff operating outside the UK and EEA who process account details and who provide support services. Transfers will only be made to countries which are the subject of an adequacy decision of the EU Commission or recipients who have entered into binding contracts with Us to comply with the terms of this Notice and Data Protection Law. By submitting your personal data, you agree to this transfer, storing, or processing. For the purposes of this Notice, Data Protection Law means (i) the UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018, (ii), for customers in the EEA, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and (iii) and any national implementing laws of the GDPR, as amended from time to time and any successor legislation to the UK GDPR, the GDPR or the Data Protection Act 2018.
We may keep records of any personal information obtained from you on or through Our Services, or otherwise, for as long as We believe is reasonably required for Our ongoing legitimate business needs, or such longer period as may be required for legal, audit and compliance purposes. This does not affect your right to opt out from receiving marketing communications, as outlined in the section “Your Rights” below.
Once you have registered an account with Us, your account details will be kept in Our database, unless deleted by you or if you ask Us to delete the details. Unless you ask Us to delete your account earlier, we will delete your account six (6) years after your account was active, if you do not instruct us not to when we email you to inform you that we intend to delete the account. When your account is deleted, we will delete all your user data related to that account.
We will retain your personal data that We process with your consent for marketing purposes until such time as your consent is withdrawn. For the avoidance of doubt, if you withdraw your consent, We will not conduct any marketing that is necessary for Our legitimate interests, although may still contact you for other purposes relating to the service or your account.
We will retain all data relating to your account, and associated queries for the applicable limitation period under applicable national laws relevant for claims for breach by Us of any contract between you and Us. Please contact Us for further information on the limitation period.
To operate Our Services, provide support, deliver content to subscribers etc., we may maintain this data, including logs and server records, as long as we provide Our Services and within the applicable limitation period relevant for claims for breach of contract.
To use data analytics and map data flows to improve Our Services, marketing, customer relationships and experiences – this data will be deleted after one year.
Notwithstanding any of the retention periods stated above, if such data is necessary to fulfil other purposes, We will keep your personal data but only to process it for such other purposes. Where We rely on the legal retention period, at the end of the legal retention period personal data stored in the databases and other electronic documents will be deleted.
We will treat your information with complete respect and will not disclose it to any third party, other than to those necessary or appropriate in connection with any of the purposes for which We use personal information, including to subcontractors or service providers, for example, service providers for payment and transaction processing or outsourced development team, that help host or support the relevant sites or application services, or otherwise provide technical assistance to Us.
We may also disclose your information to third parties as follows:
In connection with the sale or transfer of all or part of Our business.
As required by law and or in the good faith belief that disclosure is necessary to protect Our rights and/or comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, bankruptcy or similar legal process.
Where We use third party service providers as outlined above, We choose parties which We believe offer a secure service and help Us enhance Our services or practices, and follow any legal requirements that may apply.
We have put in place appropriate security measures to prevent your personal data from being accidentally lost, used or accessed in an unauthorised way, altered or disclosed, including two-factor authentication
.
In addition, We limit access to your personal data to those employees, agents, contractors and other third parties who have a business need to know. They will only process your personal data on Our instructions and they are subject to a duty of confidentiality. We have put in place procedures to deal with any suspected personal data breach and will notify you and any applicable supervisory authority of a breach where We are legally required to do so.
Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. Although We will do Our best to protect your personal data, We cannot guarantee the security of your data transmitted to Our Services; any transmission is at your own risk. Once We have received your information, We will use strict procedures and security features to try to prevent unauthorised access.
We acknowledge and respect your rights as an individual. You have the following rights:
Correction right – the right to correct inaccurate or incomplete personal data held by Us.
Erasure right – you can request erasure of your personal data if it is no longer necessary for Us to retain it for the purpose for which it was collected, if you withdraw your consent, if you have objected to Our processing and We have no other justification for processing the data, if it was processed unlawfully or if We are under a legal obligation to erase the data. If one of these grounds exist and We have no other legitimate grounds for retaining or processing your data, We will erase it without delay.
Right to object – you can object to Our processing of your data. We will stop processing the data unless We can demonstrate a compelling legitimate ground.
Restriction right – this will apply if you contest the accuracy of the personal data We hold, until We can verify its accuracy; if the processing is unlawful; if you wish Us to preserve it for a legal claim or if you object to processing based on Our or a third party’s legitimate interests, until We decide which interests prevail. We will notify you before lifting a restriction.
You have the right to make a complaint at any time to your supervisory authority. In the UK this is the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), the UK regulator for data protection issues (www.ico.org.uk). We would, however, appreciate the chance to deal with your concerns before you approach the ICO so please contact Us in the first instance.
If you wish to exercise any of your lawful rights or have questions in this regard, please reach out to Us via the contact details provided below. We may need to verify your identity before We are able to respond.
You have the right to ask Us not to process your personal data for marketing purposes. You may also choose not to receive publications or certain other communications from Us at any time by opting-out by email or via direct marketing emails sent to you.
Our Products may, from time to time, contain links to and from other websites. If you follow a link to any of these websites, please note that these websites have their own privacy policies and that We do not accept any responsibility or liability for these policies. Please check these policies before you submit any personal data to these websites.
Where We collect your personal data via Our Services, We will provide notice at or before the point of collection so that you are aware of how your data is being used. Any data collected through Our Services will be used for marketing and/or sales purposes as appropriate.
You have the right to request that We provide you with a list of the categories of your personal data We hold, the categories of sources from which We have obtained this data, and the categories of third parties that We may share this data with. You can make a request by submitting a written request to the contact details below.
We do not sell your personal data as defined under the California Consumer Privacy Act.
We recognise the privacy interests of children and encourage parents and guardians to take an active role in their children’s online activities and interests. Individuals younger than 18, but of the required age for consent to use online services, may not register for Our Services, but may have a parent or guardian register for services and help them access appropriate content.
In accordance with GDPR and the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”), Our services are not intended for use by children and We do not knowingly request, solicit, access or receive personally information (as defined in the GDPR and COPPA, as applicable) from anyone under the age of 16 and 13 respectively unless We have parental consent or consent of the child’s guardian. Where We are aware that any personal information submitted through Our Services belongs to a child and We do not have parental or guardian’s consent, We will delete this personal information from Our records. We also comply with other age restrictions and requirements in accordance with applicable local laws.
We reserve the right to change this Privacy Notice at any time to reflect changes in the law, Our data collection and use practices, the features of Our service, or advances in technology. Any changes We may make to Our Privacy Notice in the future will be posted on this page and, where appropriate, notified to you by email. Please check back frequently to see any updates or changes to Our Notice.
Please feel free to contact Us if you have any questions about Our Privacy Notice or the information practices of the services.
